cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on social media systems and the factors that lead community members to satisfy a request. It draws from social psychology literature and extracts high-level social features from text to predict the success of requests. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
